  <h2 id='field-notes'>Field Notes</h2>
  <Collapse title='Why I Work on AI for Papua'>
    Papua holds more than 250 living languages — each with its own worldview. Many are at risk of
    fading, and with them, entire epistemologies. My goal isn’t just to “save data,” but to <em
      >create digital spaces where these languages can live, evolve, and be heard again</em
    >.
  </Collapse>
  <Collapse title='What Inspires Me'>
    The meeting point of computation and culture. I’m fascinated by how neural networks mimic the
    structure of oral storytelling — pattern, rhythm, memory.
  </Collapse>
  <Collapse title='On Building Alone (and with AI)'>
    For now, it’s mostly just me and my AI tools working together to prototype, test, and iterate.
    But this solitude has its rhythm. It allows for deep thinking, steady building, and long nights
    of coffee-fueled debugging.
  </Collapse>

